The paper introduces a new dataset for document OCR from low-quality images captured by handheld mobile devices. The dataset contains images with various visual quality and artifacts, making it challenging for OCR methods. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks for text recognition, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the evaluation methodology and testset, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories.
